import { Modal, Button, Form } from "react-bootstrap";
import { useState } from "react";

const VerticallyCenteredModal = ({ show, onHide }) => {
  const [programmer, setProgrammer] = useState("");

  return (
    <Modal
      show={show}
      onHide={onHide}
      size="lg"
      aria-labelledby="contained-modal-title-vcenter"
      centered
    >
      <Modal.Header closeButton>
        <Modal.Title>Edit Bugs</Modal.Title>
      </Modal.Header>
      <Modal.Body>
        <Form>
          <Form.Group>
            <Form.Label>Brower</Form.Label>
            <Form.Select onChange={(e) => setPro(e.target.value)} required>
              <option value="">Select your Brower</option>
              <option value="Google Chrome">Google Chrome</option>
              <option value="Internet Exploer">Internet Exploer</option>
              <option value="Safari">Safari</option>
              <option value="Firefox">Firefox</option>
              <option value="Microsoft Edge">Microsoft Edge</option>
              <option value="Opera">Opera</option>
            </Form.Select>
          </Form.Group>
        </Form>
      </Modal.Body>
      <Modal.Footer>
        <Button variant="secondary" onClick={onHide}>
          Close
        </Button>
        <Button variant="primary">Save changes</Button>
      </Modal.Footer>
    </Modal>
  );
};

export default VerticallyCenteredModal;
